RabbitMQ doesn't automatically propagate W3C `traceparent`/`tracestate` headers — you must inject them on publish and extract on consume. Here's the pattern:

**Publisher (Service A)** — inject context into message headers:

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;

// Create an ActivitySource for your app
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceA.Messaging");

// When publishing:
using var activity = Source.StartActivity("order.publish", ActivityKind.Producer);

var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

// Inject current trace context
if (Activity.Current != null)
{
    props.Headers["traceparent"] = Activity.Current.Id;
    props.Headers["tracestate"]  = Activity.Current.TraceStateString ?? "";
}

channel.BasicPublish(exchange, routingKey, props, body);
```

**Consumer (Service B)** — extract context and link the span:

```csharp
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceB.Messaging");

// In your consumer callback:
var headers = ea.BasicProperties.Headers;

ActivityContext parentCtx = default;
if (headers != null
    && headers.TryGetValue("traceparent", out var raw)
    && raw is byte[] bytes)
{
    var traceparent = Encoding.UTF8.GetString(bytes);
    ActivityContext.TryParse(traceparent, null, out parentCtx);
}

using var activity = Source.StartActivity(
    "order.process",
    ActivityKind.Consumer,
    parentCtx          // ← links this span to the producer's trace
);

// Process the message — all downstream spans inherit the trace ID
```

**Wire up OpenTelemetry in `Program.cs`** (both services):

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t
        .AddSource("ServiceA.Messaging")   // or ServiceB.Messaging
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());
```

**Key points:**

- RabbitMQ headers store values as `byte[]`, so decode with `Encoding.UTF8.GetString`.
- The magic is passing `parentCtx` to `StartActivity` — this makes the consumer span a **child** of the producer span, stitching the end-to-end trace.
- If you use **MassTransit** or **NServiceBus**, they do this injection/extraction automatically. The manual approach above is for the raw `RabbitMQ.Client` library.
- Consider the [`OpenTelemetry.Api` propagator API](https://opentelemetry.io/docs/languages/net/instrumentation/#primitives) (`Propagators.DefaultTextMapPropagator.Inject/Extract`) for a more standards-compliant approach that also handles baggage.
